---
import MarketingLayout from '../layouts/MarketingLayout.astro';
export const prerender = true;
---
<MarketingLayout title="MRX Communication Preferences and Consent" description="Manage Mineral Rights Xchange email, appointment-text, optional marketing-text, and requested-call preferences or contact MRX about a consent record." path="/communication-preferences/" pageType="utility" pageCategory="legal" breadcrumbs={[{name:'Home',path:'/'},{name:'Communication Preferences',path:'/communication-preferences/'}]}>
  <section class="mrx-section"><div class="container container--prose"><p class="mrx-eyebrow">You stay in control</p><h1>Communication preferences</h1><p>MRX records email, appointment-text, optional marketing-text, and requested-call choices separately. Marketing text permission is optional and is not required to ask Tommy or book a phone call.</p><h2>Text messages</h2><p>Reply STOP to an MRX text to opt out of that text program. Reply HELP for assistance. Message frequency varies, and message and data rates may apply.</p><h2>Email and calls</h2><p>Use the unsubscribe link in an MRX marketing email, update your preference during a conversation, or email <a href="mailto:review@mineralrightsxchange.com">review@mineralrightsxchange.com</a>. A requested appointment call may still occur unless the appointment is cancelled.</p><h2>Review your stored choices</h2><p>Sign in to your <a href="/account/">private MRX account</a> or contact MRX to request a copy or correction of a permission record.</p></div></section>
</MarketingLayout>
